PROJECT NAME:
nodejs-expressjs-fundamentals-practice

PROJECT SUMMARY:
Practice-based learning project for Node.js and Express.js fundamentals with a clean and modular structure.

PROJECT DESCRIPTION:
This is a Node.js and Express.js practice project created to learn backend concepts step by step.
Each concept is organized in a separate folder with its own app.js file.
Only one concept is run at a time by uncommenting its import in index.js.
This structure helps in understanding each concept independently without mixing code
or using comment/uncomment inside a single file.

--------------------------------------------------

CONCEPTS COVERED:

- First App with Node js (Hello World)
- Create Server in Node js
- Make Simple API in Node js
- Understand Request Params
- Load HTML file & show Output
- Submit form in Node js
- Modules and Routes
- Path Module & Path constants
- Express JS setup
- Render HTML file in Express JS
- 404 Page in Express JS
- Add CSS with Express JS
- Middleware (Method 1 & 2)
- Route Middleware
- External Middleware (Morgan)
- Error Handling Middleware
- Template Engine (EJS)
- MVC Architecture
- Dynamic Routes
- API with Dynamic Routes

--------------------------------------------------

CONCEPT FOLDER MAPPING:

