--------------------------------------------------

NODE_MODULES NOTE:

The node_modules folder contains all installed dependencies required to run this project.
This folder is not included in the GitHub repository.
It is generated automatically after installing packages.

COMMAND TO INSTALL node_modules:
npm install

--------------------------------------------------

REQUIRED PACKAGES & COMMANDS:

1) Express.js
Used to create server, routes, and handle requests and responses.
Command:
npm install express

2) EJS (Template Engine)
Used to render dynamic HTML pages and pass data from server to UI.
Command:
npm install ejs

3) Morgan (External Middleware)
Used for logging HTTP requests in the console.
Command:
npm install morgan

4) Nodemon (Development Dependency)
Used to automatically restart the server when file changes occur.
Command:
npm install nodemon --save-dev

INSTALL ALL PACKAGES TOGETHER:
npm install express ejs morgan
npm install nodemon --save-dev

--------------------------------------------------

HOW TO RUN THE PROJECT:

Run with Node.js:
node index.js

Run with Nodemon (Recommended):
npx nodemon index.js

--------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT NOTES:

- Only ONE app.js should be active at a time
- Uncomment the required concept import in index.js
- Keep all other imports commented to avoid port conflicts
- node_modules is ignored using .gitignore

--------------------------------------------------

TECHNOLOGIES USED:

- Node.js
- Express.js
- EJS
- Morgan
- JavaScript (ES Modules)

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT PURPOSE:

- Build strong fundamentals in backend development
- Understand Express.js concepts clearly and independently
- Maintain a clean and revision-friendly learning structure
- Prepare for real-world backend projects

--------------------------------------------------
